WEBVTT

00:01.800 --> 00:04.310
I believe there are things
beyond comprehension.

00:04.320 --> 00:06.910
Is one of those things
god? I don't know.

00:06.950 --> 00:09.860
Why do you find it hard to believe?

00:10.596 --> 00:12.630
Wherever they went,
wherever they took rachel,

00:12.665 --> 00:13.798
They could be anywhere by now.

00:13.833 --> 00:15.618
We keep asking where they took her,

00:15.653 --> 00:16.963
But we haven't asked why.

00:16.998 --> 00:18.239
Can you tell me where I am?

00:18.274 --> 00:20.564
A waiting room. A waiting room for what?

00:20.599 --> 00:23.089
We remove the genetic
information, put it in vitro,

00:23.124 --> 00:24.424
And let natural birth occur.

00:24.459 --> 00:26.416
And she carries the child. Now it's time

00:26.451 --> 00:29.232
With the one that'll
actually bear the son of god.

00:29.267 --> 00:30.702
Rachel, where
- Where are you?

00:30.737 --> 00:32.101
I'm in some monastery somewhere.

00:32.137 --> 00:34.710
I brought some people to
see you. They can help.

00:34.745 --> 00:35.962
We're gonna go there,

00:35.997 --> 00:37.990
And we're gonna bring rachel home.

00:38.986 --> 00:40.770
Something's happening.

00:40.805 --> 00:42.520
I want to be fixed.

00:42.555 --> 00:45.336
I can fix you, but you
need to do one last thing.

00:45.371 --> 00:47.909
You want me to kill.

00:55.256 --> 00:57.829
<i>Zero is the number of mystery,</i>

00:57.864 --> 01:00.368
<i>An hour with no friend.</i>

01:00.403 --> 01:03.225
<i>Sometimes it's the beginning.</i>

01:03.260 --> 01:06.048
<i>Sometimes it's the end.</i>

